			<a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/video/archive/2011/10/you-are-data-4mb-to-be-exact/247338/"><img src="http://cdn.theatlantic.com/static/easel/images/navbars/060039_data_nav.png" alt="You Are Data&amp;mdash;4MB to be Exact" title="You Are Data&amp;mdash;4MB to be Exact" width="55" /></a>
			
			<h4 class="headline"><a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/video/archive/2011/10/you-are-data-4mb-to-be-exact/247338/">You Are Data&mdash;4MB to be Exact</a></h4>

			<span class="author"><span class="authors"><a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/kasia-cieplak-mayr-von-baldegg/" class="author" >Kasia Cieplak-Mayr von Baldegg</a></span></span>
		</div><!-- /linkContent -->
		<div class="linkContent">
			<a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/video/archive/2011/10/from-spear-hunting-to-space-travel-a-music-video-about-evolution/246814/"><img src="http://cdn.theatlantic.com/static/easel/images/navbars/122240_murf_nav.png" alt="From Spear Hunting to Space Travel" title="From Spear Hunting to Space Travel" width="55" /></a>
			
